In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses several topics including the March Madness enrollment push for the Affordable Care Act, the situation in Ukraine, the NSA's ability to record phone calls, and the missing Malaysian flight MH370. Carney emphasizes that the United States condemns Russia's moves to formally annex Crimea and that there will be costs for such actions. He also mentions that the US is focused on supporting Ukraine and working with Congress to provide the necessary resources. Carney does not comment on the specific sanctions imposed on Russia or the potential for Russia to rejoin the G8. Regarding the missing flight, Carney states that the US is working closely with the Malaysian government on the investigation and that there are no specific details on the fate of the flight at this time.